-- Russia's Sberbank arranges 870 mln euro loan for Slovenske Elektrarne
-- By Oksana Kobzeva
-- Tue Jun 10, 2014 06:05AM EDT
-- None



MOSCOW, June 10 (Reuters) - Russia's top lender Sberbank <SBER.MM> said on Tuesday it had arranged an 870 million euro ($1.18 billion) loan for Slovak electricity firm Slovenske Elektrarne.

The loan to Slovenske Elektrarne, which is controlled by Italian utility Enel <ENEI.MI>, is for seven and a half years, the bank said in a statement.